title: Faculty Member Interview
Interview Descriptions: teaching demonstration and group panel.  also meet with VP of academic services. you will have the opportunity to tour campus and meet other faculty members. i felt welcome and that the hiring committee was invested and engaged in the process
Interview Questions: Why did you close to apply at highline ?

title: Finance Office Assistant Interview
Interview Descriptions: Applied for a different position that filled internally and was offered the next available fit. Everyone was very friendly and professional. I did not feel any preconceived judgment, it was a very fair and neutral environment.
Interview Questions: Where do you see yourself in 5 years?

title: Program Coordinator Interview
Application Type: I applied through college or university. I interviewed at Highline College
Interview Descriptions: It was an over skype business call. I spoke with a hiring committee and then to the dean of students. They had a series of questions but prior to the interview, I had a to prepare a powerpoint presentation on how I would make changes or improvements to the program.
Interview Questions: What experiences contributes to this job position?

title: Instructor Interview
Application Type: I applied through an employee referral. The process took 3 weeks. I interviewed at Highline College (Des Moines, WA) in Jan 2019
Interview Descriptions: Excellent 1st round of panelists and questions. They made it a great experience and I would recommend taking the time to understand the full potential of the position you are applying for.

title: Tutor Interview
Application Type: I applied online. The process took 1 week. I interviewed at Highline College in Jan 2019
Interview Descriptions: The employer was nice and simple, with useful instruction and guidance for new people.  Moreover, enjoyable and fun, and the atmosphere was not stressed out or terrifying the candidates much.
Interview Questions: Why do you want to choose the job?

title: Program Coordinator Interview
Application Type: I applied online. The process took 2 weeks. I interviewed at Highline College (Des Moines, WA) in Oct 2017
Interview Descriptions: Email to inform me applications were being reviewed. Phone call for interview then confirmation email wirh the individuals who were in the screening committee with agenda for interview. Background check, screening committee interview, meeting with VP academic affairs 1.5 hour interview process. Offered position 2 days later by HR.
Interview Questions: How i would best support a team member with a problem with a student.

title: Front Desk Agent Interview
Application Type: I applied through an employee referral. The process took 1 day. I interviewed at Highline College (Des Moines, WA) in Dec 2016
Interview Descriptions: Easy process. Just submit online, go to the interview and answer. You will get hired. They give the flexible schedule, good pay, good hours. No benefits but it's a good on-campus job.

title: Program Assistant Interview
Application Type: I applied online. The process took 3 weeks. I interviewed at Highline College in Feb 2015
Interview Descriptions: I first received a brief phone interview after applying online. Next, a interview with  panel of about 6 people all from different departments conducted an interview with me. The atmosphere was fairly cordial. Lastly, I had an interview with the Vice President of my department, and the director. They were kind and warm, and difficullt to read!

title: Proctor/Administrative Assistant Interview
Application Type: The process took 1 day. I interviewed at Highline College (Tukwila, WA) in May 2014
Interview Descriptions: I had my interview with the Supervisor and her boss at the time. It seemed to be rather quick. They just asked me about my previous jobs and what types of computer programs that I know. I was basically told at the interview that I had the position, the hours they thought I would be working and what the job position requirement were. The whole process took about less than 40 minutes, and then I was shown around to where I would soon be working.
Interview Questions:
What kind of computer programs do you know?

How do you deal with difficult people?

What type of work did I previously do?

title: Public Safety Officer Interview
Application Type: I applied online. The process took 2+ months. I interviewed at Highline College (Des Moines, WA) in Aug 2013
Interview Descriptions: I filled out the application online and was notified for an interview several weeks later. I sat in on a committee that consisted of people from all over the campus who had an interest in who would be hired. They asked specific questions about my background, experience, core values and what I thought about diversity and inclusion.
Interview Questions: How do you define diversity and what experience do you have in working with diverse populations?

title: Head Volleyball Club Coach Interview
Application Type: I applied in-person. The process took 1 week. I interviewed at Highline College (Des Moines, WA) in Oct 2011
Interview Descriptions: Local clubs always put out coaching offers/opportunities to the local college teams because coaching is only part time work and as a collegiate player we have the skills and knowledge to coach the sport we play. I was approached by the director of South End Jrs Volleyball Club and asked if I would be interested the position of a 15's club coach. I was interviewed by the 2 club owners John and Chris and was ultimately offered the position. I had to attend one coaching seminar in order to become certified as a club coach and I also had to pass a background check.
Interview Questions: How would you respond to an unhappy parent?
